luding yours    Click on OPEN on the bottom right of the screen 8  On the left  you ll see folders  On the right hand side of the page    start writing  If you have something already written in MS Word    and perhaps saved on the M drive  open the word document and   do a cut or copy paste into your FrontPage document  How to link to another page  1  Compose something to lead your reader to another site  such as    Click here for  Select your words and click on the globe chain   combination on your toolbar  right below HELP  You ll see your   cursor blinking at the bottom of the box  Enter the address to   which you are linking and type OK  2  If you do not know the exact address  and who would  there   are two ways to accomplish this    1  First  minimize Front Page and open Internet Explorer and you should   see the VMI website  Select the  url  and  edit copy   or  Control C    Maximize Front Page again and either  edit paste  or  control P  the   address into the URL box     You can learn this same information in another page by right clicking   looking at PROPERTIES  You will see the address  but it may be   grayed out  If so  select it and press  control C   copy  then  paste   it into the URL box    2  Select the words  click here for  for example  and click on the globe ball   as if you were making a link  A window appears and at the bottom  you   see the  URL  box where you will enter the address  To the right  you   see a colorful icon of a world with a magnifying glass  Click on it and    it will open Windows Explorer  Type in your favorite search engine    for example  http www google com or just type the letter y  add a   space  and type in a keyword  and search for something that interests   you  dogs  universities  travel  etc  The URL box automatically tracks    what you look at  so when you have decided on the page  click on the    scroll with red feather  at the bottom of your screen  and the address   automatically pops into the box  Click OK  Let s have some fun  COLORS  To select the color for your background  nobody likes an ugly homepage  click FORMAT and background  A window pops up  On the left you will see a box for BACKGROUND colors  In the drop down box  curse down  If you do not like what you see  click on CUSTOM and design your own colors by moving the color wheel up down side side until you see a color in the big box that suits  On the LEFT  click on OK and your background should change  The same will work for your font  Click FORMAT  font  and select your style or color  WARNING  If you choose to keep your text WHITE  nobody can print your page  The letters won t show up  SAVE YOUR PAGE  Click File and SAVE AS  Double click the folder that has your name on it  Name your file something easy such as Bobfilm htm Make sure you have  htm after your title  Click on SAVE  If you would like to see how your page looks while you are still editing  look on the bottom left of your screen and you will see a  Preview  button  Click it and you should see your work as it will appear online  Once you look at it  click again on NORMAL  and this will take you back to the editor   Sometimes in SS 418 this does not work  Don t fret  If you want to preview your page and the preview button does not work  right click  Select properties and you will see your URL grayed out  Select it   Control C   Paste in an email or a word document  It should automatically turn blue and be underlined  Double click it and your page should appear  This will get you started  Col  Bulger Barnett Home Courses VMI Spanish Drills Links of Interest Applications   Forms Language Skills VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation